    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "Another reason for using package-info.java instead of package.html could be that .java does not imply a specific output format of the documentation. For example you might want to output the javadoc as LaTeX or as a PDF file. Depending of javadoc compiler implementation this could cause problems in the .html case."
