  "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/questions/3644726/javadoc-package-html-or-package-info-java",
  "title" : "Javadoc: package.html or package-info.java",
  "body" : "<p>When trying to create package level Javadoc comments, whats the preferred method? What do you do?</p>\n\n<p><strong>package-info.java</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Pros\n\n<ul>\n<li>Newer</li>\n</ul></li>\n<li>Cons\n\n<ul>\n<li>Abuse of a class - Classes are for code, not for only comments</li>\n</ul></li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>package.html</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Pros\n\n<ul>\n<li>HTML extension means its not code</li>\n<li>Syntax highlighting in IDE's/text editors</li>\n</ul></li>\n<li>Cons\n\n<ul>\n<li>None?</li>\n</ul></li>\n</ul>\n\n<hr>\n\n<p>For me, I've always used Package.html. But I'm wondering if its the correct choice. </p>\n"
}